article.description: Scott scores 23; Idaho beats S Dakota St 82-77
article.headline: Scott scores 23; Idaho beats S Dakota St 82-77
article.linkText: Scott scores 23; Idaho beats S Dakota St 82-77
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- Mike Scott scored 23 points and Bira Seck added 13 points and 12 rebounds to help Idaho beat South Dakota State 82-77 on Monday night. Idaho (2-0) trailed 74-75 when Scott found Perrion Callandret for a 3-pointer with 56 seconds left. South Dakota State's Skyler Flatten missed a 3 on the other end but, after grabbing the offensive rebound, Cody Larson missed a layup before Scott hit a 3-pointer coming out of a timeout to make it 80-75 with 10 seconds left. Deondre Parks got a quick layup 2 seconds later and immediately fouled Scott, who hit a pair of free throws and closed the scoring at 82-77 with 6 seconds left. Parks and Jake Bittle scored 18 apiece for South Dakota State (0-2). Larson finished with 14 points and 10 rebounds and Flatten scored 13. Idaho made 8 of 15 from behind the arc and grabbed 16 offensive rebounds.
